OL,5, The family of a father who was wrongly 
OL,6, convicted of murder have been given a  
OL,7, police apology 70 years after he was   
OL,8, executed in a British prison.          
OL,10,FMahmood Mattan, a British Somali and   
OL,11,Fformer seaman, was hanged in 1952 after
OL,12,Fhe was convicted of killing shopkeeper 
OL,13,FLily Volpert in her store in Cardiff.  
OL,15,FHis conviction was the first Criminal  
OL,16,FCase Review Commission referral to be  
OL,17,Fquashed at the Court of Appeal in 1998.
OL,19,FSouth Wales Police have apologised and 
OL,20,Fadmitted the prosecution was "flawed". 
